"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57851","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-11","<p /> <p /> <p>We are working closely with our supplier to deliver the best possible service for claimants, driving up performance and quality to help reduce waiting times and process claims as quickly as possible. We are continuing to monitor and robustly manage this contract.</p><p>We do not have a target timescale for waiting time for an Employment and Support Allowance and Incapacity Benefit Reassessment Work Capability Assessment.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","199012","2014-06-11T16:53:37.0273365Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57851/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57851/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57851/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the target waiting time is for work capability assessment for both (a) employment and support allowance and (b) incapacity benefit reassessment; and what proportion of such assessments have been carried out within the target timescale in the last four quarters for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","199013"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57852","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p /> <p>The information requested is not available.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-09T15:32:25.7404975Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57852/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57852/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57852/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households subject to the benefits cap in (a) each parliamentary constituency and (b) each local authority area in Scotland have received transitional support via discretionary housing payment to date.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","198984"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57853","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-10","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Jobcentre Plus has flexibility to meet the particular needs of claimants living in rural areas.</p><p> </p><p>For example postal signing can be offered and claimants attending interviews on days outside their normal day of attendance can have their travelling expenses reimbursed.</p><p> </p><p>Work Coaches are also able to use the Flexible Support Fund and issue Travel Discount Cards to help claimants with travel expenses.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-10T12:07:43.4511561Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57853/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57853/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57853/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Unemployed People: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will review his Department's policy on issuing travel warrants to rural residents for (a) fortnightly signing-on and (b) other interviews and advisory meetings to take account of the need for such residents to travel further than average to jobcentres.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","198988"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57854","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p>Information on the number of households subject to the benefit cap in each parliamentary constituency in Scotland have not yet been published as Official Statistics. We intend to include this information as part of an upcoming release in line with the Code of Practice for Official Statistics. Information on the number of households subject to the benefit cap in each local authority in Scotland has been published and is available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-cap-number-of-households-capped-to-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-cap-number-of-households-capped-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-09T16:01:42.095341Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57854/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57854/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57854/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Social Security Benefits: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households have been subject to the benefit cap in (a) each parliamentary constituency and (b) each local authority area in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","198982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57855","Scotland Office","false","2014-06-11","<p> </p><p>Details of the number of moves that have taken place under the HomeSwap Direct Scheme from Scotland to elsewhere in the United Kingdom in each of the last three years are not held centrally. This information is more likely to be held by social housing providers.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-06-11T15:29:34.449092Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57855/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57855/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57855/answer","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57855/answer/previousversion/200","Biography information for David Mundell","2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-06-04","Social Rented Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how many tenants in Scotland arranged mutually exchanges to elsewhere in the UK through Home Swap Direct in each of the last three years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","199058"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57856","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p /> <p /> <p>The cost of refunding travel expenditure by Jobseekers to Jobcentres in Kilmarnock and Loudoun constituency between January 2014 and May 2014 was :</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>January 2014 to May 2014</p></td><td><p>£1,456.88</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-09T15:51:55.540858Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57856/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57856/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57856/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Unemployed People: Travel","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the cost of refunding travel expenditure by jobseekers to jobcentres in Kilmarnock and Loudoun constituency was between January 2014 and May 2014.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","198918"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57857","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-11","<p /> <p /> <p>We are working closely with our supplier to deliver the best possible service for claimants, driving up performance and quality to help reduce waiting times and process claims as quickly as possible. We are continuing to monitor and robustly manage this contract.</p><p>We do not have a target timescale for waiting time for an Employment and Support Allowance and Incapacity Benefit Reassessment Work Capability Assessment.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","199013","2014-06-11T16:53:36.9163024Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57857/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57857/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57857/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to the Answer of 7 May 2014, Official Report, column 228W, on social security benefits: disability, if he will take steps to reduce the national average waiting times for work capability assessments for (a) employment and support allowance and (b) incapacity benefit reassessment.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","199012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57858","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-09","<p>The specific information requested is not collected or held centrally.</p><p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC), an independent statutory body, is responsible for the enforcement, monitoring and assessment of how public bodies comply with the public sector Equality Duty (PSED) and specific duties. The EHRC has published two reports to date which look at the performance of public bodies in England under the PSED and specific duties:</p><p>• ‘Publishing equality information: Commitment, engagement and transparency' was published in December 2012. This report looked at how public authorities had performed with regard to the first specific duty (publication of equality information). Data for this assessment was collected between February and April 2012 and covered 1,159 public authorities in England. The report indicated that about half of the public authorities reviewed were publishing equality information on their workforce and service users by April 2012. Many more (78%) were publishing information on either their staff or their service users.</p><p>• ‘Assessment of the publication of equality objectives by English public authorities' was published in Autumn 2013. This report sets out the findings of an assessment of how public authorities in England are publishing equality objectives. Data for the assessment was collected between September and December 2012 and covered 2,010 public authorities.</p><p>These reports do not estimate the associated costs of producing and publishing equalities information.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","198765","2014-06-09T16:38:25.2877513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57858/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57858/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57858/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-04","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many reports on equality information and objectives each category of public authority has published under the Equality Act 2010 (Specific Duties) Regulations 2011 in each year since the regulations came into force; and what the cost of producing those reports was for each category of public authority in each such year.","false","Biography information for Dominic Raab","Esher and Walton","Mr Dominic Raab","198764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57859","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-09","<p>The specific information requested is not collected or held centrally.</p><p>The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC), an independent statutory body, is responsible for the enforcement, monitoring and assessment of how public bodies comply with the public sector Equality Duty (PSED) and specific duties. The EHRC has published two reports to date which look at the performance of public bodies in England under the PSED and specific duties:</p><p>• ‘Publishing equality information: Commitment, engagement and transparency' was published in December 2012. This report looked at how public authorities had performed with regard to the first specific duty (publication of equality information). Data for this assessment was collected between February and April 2012 and covered 1,159 public authorities in England. The report indicated that about half of the public authorities reviewed were publishing equality information on their workforce and service users by April 2012. Many more (78%) were publishing information on either their staff or their service users.</p><p>• ‘Assessment of the publication of equality objectives by English public authorities' was published in Autumn 2013. This report sets out the findings of an assessment of how public authorities in England are publishing equality objectives. Data for the assessment was collected between September and December 2012 and covered 2,010 public authorities.</p><p>These reports do not estimate the associated costs of producing and publishing equalities information.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey","198764","2014-06-09T16:38:25.3658669Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57859/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57859/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57859/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-04","Equality","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how many public authorities in each category of public authority published equality information and objectives under the Equality Act (Specific Duties) Regulations 2011 in each year since they came into force.","false","Biography information for Dominic Raab","Esher and Walton","Mr Dominic Raab","198765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57860","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-09","<p> </p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills has not collected any quantitative information on the number of zero-hours contracts in the UK which bar any additional employment. The Chartered Institute of Personnel and Development (CIPD) suggested, in its report <em>Zero Hours Contracts: Myth and reality</em> that 9% of workers on zero hours contracts reported that they were never allowed to work for another employer when their primary employer had no work for them.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-09T15:53:07.405935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57860/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57860/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57860/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-04","Zero Hours Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what information his Department holds on the number of zero-hours contracts in the UK which bar any additional employment.","false","Biography information for Dominic Raab","Esher and Walton","Mr Dominic Raab","198782"
