"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57873","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-09","<p>I was deeply concerned to learn of the destruction of a Baha'i cemetery in Shiraz. On 14 May 2014, I made a statement on this issue, calling for Iran to abide by its international commitments to ensure all Iranians are free to practice their religion without fear of persecution. This includes protection of religious sites.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-06-09T10:35:53.1876302Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57873/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57873/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57873/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-04","Iran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will call on the Iranian authorities to halt the destruction of an historically important Bahá'i cemetary in Shiraz; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Angie Bray","Ealing Central and Acton","Angie Bray","198766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57874","Department of Health","false","2014-06-09","<p>All acute trusts have access to computerised tomography (CT) and NHS England is not aware of any patient access problems. The NHS England standards for seven day services support seven day access to CT. CT involves ionising radiation, so is a test that has to be justified and used in appropriate patient pathways.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-09T15:12:23.3197304Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57874/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57874/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57874/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-04","Tomography","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to ensure access to CT scanning is more readily available to NHS patients.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","198783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57875","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-10","<p /> <p /> <p>I refer the hon. Member to the replies given to him on 12 May 2014, Official Report, Columns 413-414W (for volume and average duration of calls), and on 10 April 2014, Official Report Columns 396-397W (for a note on money claims centres).</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-06-10T12:05:15.8750111Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57875/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57875/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57875/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-04","Courts: Telephone Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many calls were made on higher-rate telephone numbers to (a) magistrates' courts, (b) county courts and county court money claims centres in England in 2012-13 and 2013-14; and what the average duration was of calls to such numbers.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","198816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57876","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department is collecting information to understand how the introduction of mandatory reconsideration is operating, including completion timescales. However, this data is not sufficiently robust and reliable to make available.</p><p> </p><p>In the production of new statistics, which all the above would be, the Department works to guidelines set by the UK Statistics Authority to ensure we are able to publish statistics that meet the high quality standards expected. Departmental statisticians need to assure themselves of the quality of administrative data sources before releasing information as Official statistics, and before the exact timing and format of statistics can be confirmed. .</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","198667","2014-06-09T15:14:45.5778741Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57876/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57876/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57876/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many and what proportion of mandatory reconsideration periods have exceeded 14 days; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","198805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57877","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p /> <p>Appeals on the disability benefits are administered and heard by Her Majesty's Courts and Tribunals Service. Atos has no role to play.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-09T14:59:01.8050366Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57877/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57877/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57877/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects Atos to appoint new agency staff to administer appeals on reassessment of eligibility for disability benefits.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","198778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57878","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p>As with any medical condition, DWP recognises fibromyalgia as a potentially significantly disabling condition. The statistical information requested is not readily available and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-09T16:44:47.4546602Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57878/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57878/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57878/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Work Capability Assessment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what consideration is given to fibromyalgia in the work capability assessment; and how many and what proportion of people diagnosed with fibromyalgia have been declared fit for work following such an assessment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","198802"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57879","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>The Department for Transport is committed to ensuring that all disabled people have the same access to transport services and opportunities to travel as other members of society. The Public Service Vehicles Accessibility Regulations 2000 (PSVAR) outline specific requirements for the bus industry to ensure that buses are as accessible as possible for disabled passengers. Latest statistics (September 2013) show that 78% of buses in England now meet PSVAR accessibility requirements, while 92% operate with a low floor facility and these figures continue to grow steadily.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department also recognises that blind and partially sighted passengers find audio and visual announcements particularly useful when travelling on buses. We will therefore continue to encourage bus operators and local authorities to invest in audio/visual announcement systems for their buses where possible. However, we also understand that this technology comes at a considerable cost.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>With this in mind, my noble colleague, Baroness Kramer wrote to bus operators on 4<sup>th</sup> February 2014 to encourage the development of simpler, more affordable audio/visual announcement systems for buses that can provide benefits to as many passengers as possible. Alongside this, the Department for Transport is also looking into the possibility of establishing a research initiative involving small businesses and academic institutions through the <em>‘Transport Systems Catapult'</em>to encourage further innovation.</p><p> </p><p><em> </em></p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-12T10:42:09.204233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57879/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57879/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57879/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-04","Bus Services: Visual Impairment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to help blind and partially sighted passengers travel on buses.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","199038"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57880","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-09","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department cannot respond to the House of Commons with regards to a specific case.</p><p> </p><p>I will write to the hon. Gentleman.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-09T14:00:50.4057671Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57880/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57880/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57880/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Personal Independence Payment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects Mr Andrew Cottrell of Prenton, to undergo his medical examination as part of his application for the personal independence payment.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","199007"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57881","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-11","<p /> <p /> <p>Universal Jobmatch revolutionises the way jobseekers look for work and it has already helped many jobseekers find the jobs they want through the millions of vacancies posted since 2012. It is part of the government's plan for providing easy online access to government services for all.</p><p> </p><p>There are various circumstances where an employer may wish to keep their details confidential – for example, if they are employing a Personal Carer or another role where they are using their home address. We estimate that there are 42,544 employer confidential vacancies currently on Universal Jobmatch. This equates to 7.1% of the total live vacancies as at 5 June 2014.</p><p> </p><p>The security of a user's data is of the utmost importance to us and built into the service are monitoring tools and vacancy checks, which help to detect, deter and remedy inappropriate use of the site. Checks are made to identify inappropriate, fraudulent and bogus jobs and employers in order to block them from being posted.</p><p> </p><p>There are also warnings to users of the service advising them they should not be asked to reveal personal information i.e. bank details, as this information is not relevant to the application process.</p><p> </p><p>Additionally, a 'Contact Us' facility is provided so users can quickly highlight any employers that users may have concerns about. DWP then investigate such concerns.</p><p> </p><p>These checks are in place for all vacancies, including employer confidential vacancies.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-11T16:18:44.3980868Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57881/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57881/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57881/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Vacancies: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate he has made of the number and proportion of vacancies on Universal Jobsmatch classified as employer confidential; and what checks are in place to ensure that such vacancies are not bogus, fraudulent or otherwise inappropriate.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Mr Frank Field","199039"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57882","Home Office","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p>Guidance on how to certify a building for religious worship and register for <br>the solemnization of marriages was issued on 18 February 2014 by the General <br>Register Office and is available at: <br>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/281332<br>/D0550_F78L.pdf<br><br>The guidance sets out the different options that are available for places of <br>worship and registration for the solemnisation of marriage. Registration of <br>individual places of worship takes place through local registration services <br>attached to local authorities and they are expected to adhere to the guidance.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-23T11:29:36.3661875Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57882/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57882/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57882/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-04","Marriage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what guidance his Department has given to local authorities about churches and same sex marriage.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57883","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-09","<p><br>I refer the Hon. member to the answer that I gave to him on 5 March 2013, Official Report, Col 967 – 968W.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-06-09T16:57:13.5199716Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57883/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57883/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57883/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-04","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department spent on contracts for consultancy groups on the Bost Agri-Business Park and Airfield projects in Afghanistan in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012 and (d) 2013.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57884","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-09","<p> </p><p>DFID sends a variety of developmental experts to oversee projects overseas.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-06-09T16:50:17.2497931Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57884/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57884/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57884/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-04","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether it is her Department's policy to send only departmental development experts to oversee development projects overseas.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198787"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57885","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-09","<p> </p><p>Procurement tendering processes conducted by my department are completed in accordance with EU directives. Contracts are awarded following a competitive tendering process. Invitations to tender are specific to the nature of the intervention required.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-06-09T15:52:19.5227678Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57885/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57885/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57885/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-04","Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what criteria her Department uses for decisions on contracts to consultancy groups on development projects.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198788"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57886","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-09","<p>Procurement tendering processes conducted by my department are completed in accordance with EU directives. Contracts are awarded following a competitive tendering process. Invitations to tender are specific to the nature of the intervention required.</p><p>DFID has no contracts providing global services.</p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2014-06-09T16:51:20.3114032Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57886/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57886/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57886/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-04","Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many consultancy groups currently have global contracts with her Department as development implementers.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57887","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-11","<p /> <p /> <p /> <p /> <p>The Access to Work programme currently allows for support to be organised in this way if it offers the most cost effective and practical solution and there is clear customer need for that level of support. We are taking a close look at the Access to Work programme over the next three months, focussing on how we can assist the largest number of disabled paople in work. We will incude in that process a consideration of how best to address the needs of customers requiring support for a large number of hours each week on an on-going basis.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-11T16:50:29.2828316Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57887/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57887/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57887/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will amend the access to work scheme to enable deaf people to employ a full-time salaried support worker.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57888","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-11","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The Access to Work programme has not been changed in this way. No customers are required to employ a full-time support worker, their employers and support providers and we are not prescriptive on this.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-06-11T16:58:50.6067672Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57888/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57888/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57888/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-04","Access to Work Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the evidential basis was for the decision to change the Access to Work scheme in regards to deaf people having to employ a full-time salaried support worker.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","198737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57889","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-09","<p>The Department has a very thorough lessons learned process which is normally applied when an operation is initiated. However, due to operational security sensitivities we do not, as a matter of course, publish the findings of such processes. We have no plans to publish any lessons learned from Op Ellamy.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-06-09T16:58:12.7805705Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57889/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57889/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57889/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-04","Libya","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will publish his Department's assessment of lessons learned from the recent Libyan campaign.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","199068"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57890","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-09","<p>We do not possess through life cost information for individual aircraft in the Voyager fleet. Under the Voyager PFI solution the MoD is not buying aircraft but a 27 year integrated Air Transport and Air to Air Refuelling service which is underpinned by the provision of 14 aircraft, the infrastructure, personnel, training and training school (including a full mission simulator), aircraft maintenance and engineering, spares, despatch and ground support. The outturn value of the contract is £10.5 billion over 27 years, excluding fuel and other associated usage costs.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-09T16:17:21.8702558Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57890/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57890/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57890/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-04","Future Strategic Tanker Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the through life cost is for each of the 14 Voyager aircraft.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","198947"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57891","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-09","<p>The following table describes the current Ministry of Defence contracts solely for the Astute class submarine programme. All contracts, except serial 9, are with BAE Systems Marine Ltd. Once in service, platforms, including the Astute class, are supported via extant Fleet wide arrangements.<br><br>Serial Contract Description<br>1 Batch 1 The build of Astute boats 1-3.<br>2 Boat 4 The build of Astute boat 4.<br>3 Boat 5 The provision of long-lead materials and activities to support the build of Astute boat 5.<br>4 Boat 6 The provision of long-lead materials and activities to support the build of Astute boat 6.<br>5 Boat 7 The provision of long-lead materials and activities to support the build of Astute boat 7.<br>6 Base Spares To provide the initial spares provisioning for Astute boats leaving Barrow.<br>7 Foundation Placed to deliver the savings required by the 2010 SDSR through performance improvement and cost-benefit initiatives. To note that this contract impacts on both the Astute and Successor programmes.<br>8 Submarine Design Services The provision of In Service technical assistance.<br>9 Astute Class Training Service A PFI contract for the provision of Astute class crew training. The contract is placed with FAST Training Services Ltd (a consortium of BAE Systems, L-3 Communications and Babcock International).</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-09T16:54:27.170279Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57891/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57891/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57891/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-04","Astute Class Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what contracts are outstanding in the Astute programme.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","198946"
