t be clear what the potential consequential impacts on service quality, sustainability (financial and clinical) and potential unintended changes to patient pathways will be. Until the review is complete NHS England has said no substantive changes will be made to the current provision.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-09T13:46:31.657",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57918/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57918/answer","Hansard extract 24032014 Radiotherapy.docx","Hansard extract 24032014 Radiotherapy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57918/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-04","Radiotherapy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Answer of 24 March 2014, Official Report, column 132W, on radiotherapy, and with reference to section 3 of the guidance issued by Monitor on the Commissioning of Radiosurgery Services on 4 April 2014, for what reasons NHS England is not funding patients to be treated with the gamma knife at University College Hospital London.","false","Biography information for Tessa Munt","Wells","Tessa Munt","198760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57919","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-16","<p>The annual percentage increases awarded by the Armed Forces Pay Review Body for the starting rates of pay of the specified ranks are shown in the table below. There was no annual percentage increase in 2011 and 2012 but all privates were awarded a £250 rise. <br><br></p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-16T14:32:02.1141029Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57919/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57919/answer","20140616 - 198821 Stephen Doughty.doc","Table - Part of answer to 198821","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57919/answer","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57919/answer/previousversion/256","Biography information for Anna Soubry","11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-04","Armed Forces: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what annual percentage increases in starting rates of pay (a) lieutenant colonels, (b) majors, (c) captains, (d) lieutenants, (e) sergeants, (f) corporals and (g) privates in the Army have received since 1982.","false","Biography information for Stephen Doughty","Cardiff South and Penarth","Stephen Doughty","198821"
