ank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/insolvency-statistics-january-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Annual numbers and rates of bankruptcies by region for 2000-2012 are available in the <em>Individual Insolvencies by Region</em> publication, which can be found at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/insolvency-statistics-individual-insolvencies-by-region" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/insolvency-statistics-individual-insolvencies-by-region</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Cardiff Central","Jenny Willott",,"2014-06-09T16:00:50.5838249Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57947/answer","Biography information for Jenny Willott","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57947/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57947/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-04","Insolvency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many insolvencies there were in each (a) region of England and (b) London borough in (i) 2011-12, (ii) 2012-13 and (iii) 2013-14; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Mr Gareth Thomas","199141"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57948","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-09","<p>In July 2013 the Government announced that it had reached an agreement with the major UK banks to publish lending data across 10,000 individual postcodes.</p><p> </p><p>The first dataset was published in December 2013 and shows the outstanding stock of lending that has been committed to customers across three categories; loans and overdrafts to SMEs, mortgages and unsecured personal loans (excluding credit cards).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The data will allow challenger banks, smaller building societies, credit unions and community development finance institutions (CDFIs) to find areas where there is a lack of lending so they can offer finance to those customers who are crying out for support to help their business grow.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","199106 ; 199107 ; 199138","2014-06-09T14:11:46.9674785Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57948/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57948/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57948/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-04","Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will require the Prudential Regulation Authority to conduct an analysis of recently released personal and business lending data by postcode to examine (a) levels of disparity in lending and (b) progress in achieving financial inclusion; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Mr Gareth Thomas","199137"
