"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57960","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-11","<p>The Government supports an open internet, and believes that self-regulation is the best approach to achieve this. We expect ISPs to be transparent with their customers regarding their terms and conditions at the point of sale, including any traffic management practices, in order to allow consumers to make an informed choice and consider any alternative providers.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-06-11T14:48:16.6536402Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57960/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57960/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57960/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-04","Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what his policy is on allowing internet service providers to restructure charging arrangements for faster network access.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","198725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57961","Department of Health","false","2014-06-11","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State for Health is planning to meet with the Chair in the near future, to discuss the health system and emergency medicine. The Chair also met with my noble friend the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State (Earl Howe) last week to discuss operational resilience plans for the remainder of this year.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-11T15:57:06.920004Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57961/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57961/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57961/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-04","College of Emergency Medicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to meet the Chair of the College of Emergency Medicine.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","198738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57962","Northern Ireland Office","false","2014-06-09","<p> </p><p>I have met the Northern Ireland Minister for Social Development twice in the last 12 months.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Chipping Barnet","Mrs Theresa Villiers",,"2014-06-09T15:28:49.9926055Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57962/answer","Biography information for Theresa Villiers","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57962/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57962/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2014-06-04","Northern Ireland Government","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many times she has met the Northern Ireland Minister for Social Development in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Mr Ivan Lewis","Bury South","Mr Ivan Lewis","198757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57963","Department of Health","false","2014-06-11","<p>Currently donated lungs are allocated to the designated cardiothoracic transplant centres on a zonal basis. However, the Cardiothoracic Organs Advisory Group (CTAG) have recently reviewed the allocation policy and have recommended that the size of the allocation zones be adjusted to help ensure equity of access. NHS Blood and Transplant (NHSBT) have therefore confirmed that for cardiothoracic organs, the zones will be reviewed in August 2014 to coincide with changes in liver allocation zones and from August 2015, heart and lung zones will be disaggregated and the zones reviewed separately.</p><p> </p><p>CTAG have also recommended that NHSBT reviews the consequences of introducing two levels of priority for listing for lung transplants - urgent and routine, and suggest a national allocation scheme for urgent listed patients, and zonal allocation for routine listed patients.</p><p> </p><p>Any proposed change would need to be validated by NHSBT, who will review the criteria for urgent listing and the statistical modelling of the potential impact of such a system. NHSBT will continue to work closely with the Cystic Fibrosis Trust to improve outcomes for patients requiring lung transplants.</p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2014-06-11T15:43:54.7503328Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57963/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57963/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57963/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-04","Cystic Fibrosis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Cystic Fibrosis Trust's report entitled Hope for More: Improving access to lung transplantation and care for people with cystic fibrosis, what assessment he has made of the donor lung utilisation rate for transplantation; and what measures he has identified as having the greatest potential to increase such utilisation.","false","Biography information for Julian Sturdy","York Outer","Julian Sturdy","199027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57964","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-10","<p>It would not be appropriate for the Foreign and Commonwealth Office to discuss the details of an individual case. However, consular officials have provided full consular assistance to Mr Zeidan since we were informed of his detention and will continue to do so. In any case where we have concerns about the welfare or human rights of a British National, with their permission, we will raise these.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-06-10T11:38:42.9191392Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57964/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57964/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57964/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-04","United Arab Emirates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will make representations to the government of the United Arab Emirates to ensure that Ahmad Zeidan is given his full legal rights and protections whilst in the custody of that government.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","198717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57965","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-10","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office takes allegations of mistreatment of any British national overseas extremely seriously. With the permission of an individual, we will always formally raise these with the host government. We have raised our concerns on a number of specific cases in the UAE and will continue to use the Ministerial Taskforce and other opportunities to raise consular issues when necessary, including those relating to British Nationals in detention.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-06-10T11:37:36.8274426Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57965/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57965/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/57965/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-04","United Arab Emirates","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will hold discussions with his counterparts in the United Arab Emirates on the alleged torture of UK citizens in UAE prisons.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","198716"
