"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58126","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-11","<p>The Government publishes quarterly official statistics relating to the Help to Buy: mortgage guarantee scheme. The first of these were published on 29 May 2014.</p><p> </p><p>This report, along with accompanying tables, can be found at: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014</p><p> </p><p>The Government also publishes monthly statistics on the number of homes purchased with the support of the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme, by local authority in England. This data can be found at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p><sup> </sup></p><p> </p><p> </p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2014-06-11T15:14:25.3765944Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58126/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58126/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58126/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-04","Help to Buy Scheme: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) Help to Buy Mortgage Guarantees and (b) Help to Buy: Equity Loans have been taken out in (i) the North West, (ii) Lancashire and (iii) Pendle to date.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","198974"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58127","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-06-11","<p> </p><p>a) Data on the Help to Buy: Mortgage Guarantee scheme are published by the Treasury. Figures to 31 March 2014 are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/help-to-buy-mortgage-guarantee-scheme-quarterly-statistics-october-2013-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>b) For the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme, figures for the average purchase price of properties are available at district council level, with the most recent official statisics relating to sales under the scheme to 30 April 2014.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(i) As outlined in the Written Ministerial Statement of 18 September 2012, <em>Official Report</em>, Column 32WS, my Department no longer publishes statistics by government office region</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(ii) The average figure for that period across the twelve district council areas of Lancashire is £176,888. The figure for Lancashire can be compared with a national average of £205,424, as published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>(iii) In Pendle, only one sale had been completed by 30 April 2014, and so quoting the average figure for that area would lead to disclosure of the purchase price of that property. This might be regarded as creating an unacceptably high risk of disclosing personal data and a statistical distortion.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Figures for the numbers of sales under the Help to Buy equity loan scheme as at 30 April 2014 broken down by local authority and postcode sector are available at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistical-data-sets/help-to-buy-equity-loan-scheme-monthly-statistics</a>. I have also placed a copy of the table in the Library of the House .</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2014-06-11T16:46:36.0269768Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58127/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58127/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58127/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-04","Help to Buy Scheme: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what the average price has been for houses sold under (a) the Help to Buy: Mortgage Guarantee and (b) the Help to Buy: Equity Loan scheme in (i) the North West, (ii) Lancashire and (iii) Pendle.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","198937"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58128","Department of Health","false","2014-06-11","<p>NHS England has advised that information about the number of funding applications, the number of applications which have been approved and the number of applications which include a rent increase is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>However, NHS England has been collating all applications transferred from predecessor primary care trusts concerning funding for general practitioner (GP) practice premises, after which prioritisation decisions will be made for each of the application categories in the system.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England is working with clinical commissioning groups, health and wellbeing boards and other partners to develop a new strategy for premises and to support timely decisions on GP premises funding.</p><p> </p>","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Daniel Poulter","198719","2014-06-11T15:20:35.130722Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58128/answer","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58128/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58128/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-04","GP Surgeries: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many funding applications were made by GPs for new premises in 2013; and how many of such applications have been approved by NHS England.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jowell","Dulwich and West Norwood","Dame Tessa Jowell","198718"
